    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You must be in the Shunpo stance to use this technique. You take a number of Shunpo leaps equal to a move action in a straight line, and each creature standing adjacent to a square you pass through suffers 3d6 damage and is pushed back 5 feet. Unlike normal Shunpo movement, you can be easily spotted while moving.<br><br>You can make fewer leaps if you wish, though you must make at least 2 leaps.</p>\n\n\n\n",
